subject: Add BMC table missing properties
commitMessage:
Add BMC table missing properties

- Added the following properties: Name, Spare part number,
Manufacturer type, Manager type, BMC date and time, Last reset time,
Identify led

Signed-off-by: Sandeepa Singh <sandeepa.singh@ibm.com>
Change-Id: I6d84f867f3c272f3989f76c86f054f143b8b1bbd

Patch Set 28: Commit message was updated.
Change has been successfully merged by Derick Montague
Are you going to change this to section-divider?
Yes, I will change the class to section-divider once the processors table story  https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/webui-vue/+/42506 is merged.

You added a section-divider class in https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/webui-vue/+/42506/4/src/views/Health/HardwareStatus/HardwareStatusTableProcessors.vue#84. Should we use that instead of bmc-section and also add the margin properties to the declaration block to keep the margin values consistent in all tables?
Yes, I have placed margins in the section-divider class now. I will remove this once the processors table story is merged.
I don't think we should call CCIN
CCIN is Customer card identification number I believe and is not used outside of IBM/Power arch.

maybe we can remove the class="ml-4" on each <dt> and instead wrap this entire block in a div with the class class="ml-4"

Right now the dt and dd margins do not align when shrinking the screen size
where is this coming from? I don't see this coming from the store?
Not sure we should be calling it a Fru number. The Redfish API calls it a spare part number. Can we use that name?
Let's discuss with our users. We should call it sparePartNumber upstream and if it doesn't resonate with our users, we can change it downstream. Please talk to Pari or Priyanka.
We need to call this Spare part number.
I think we should have error handling & toasts
I discussed with the designers, they said we don't need toasts messages on toggling Identify LED. But I have added a catch block to console error if any.
As per designers, no toasts messages required here.
It is expected that the other option for this is undefined? That test might be more clear. You could show if not undefined. Either fix or ack if you want to move forward and I'll +1 and submit.

The switch will show up only when LocationIndicatorActive is either true or false. In all other cases such as undefined, no value or the key is not present, the else block will execute to display '--'.
Right now code for identify led has not been merged, so to show up '--' until we have it merged. I was planning to remove it in separate story so that at least this story can be merged. Thoughts?
I'm ok with this for the v-if, maybe leave a comment saying it will be removed when backend megred
Leaving comments in the code for clarity.
What should the term definition be associated with if removed?

@Derick MDN uses this format in "Multiple terms, single description"
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl#multiple_terms_single_description
I'll remove it, left it by mistake. Thanks!
This is not valid HTML. A <dl> should only contain <dt> and <dd> elements.

@Derick I thought so too, but MDN includes Wrapping name-value groups in div elements:
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl#wrapping_name-value_groups_in_htmlelementdiv_elements

That is a good catch. I didn't realize that. It is odd since you can't do that with ordered or unordered lists. This would have been an easy way to handle our solution for removing the
tag without using floats. I acknowledged the first comment about the disparate
. I fully understand the grouping of multiple terms with a single description, but is this our intent? Is the intent for Graphical console and Connect types supported to be multiple terms for the definition of Connect types? Same question for Serial console. Example: https://imgur.com/a/KxF3TTX

I get your point @Derick, technically speaking Graphical console and Connect types supported are not multiple terms for the definition of connect types. I tried using

or

or heading tags but then the size of the font changes. I guess this was the reason Graphical console was previously kept in dt.
The most likely way to fix this would be to create a new <dl> and use a heading tag before and then use a utility class to change the size.
